This is the over all task for Shell, init files, variables and expansions. And the following scripts are written in order to do the tasks.
|FILENAME|DESCRIPTION|

|-----|-------|

0 | `0-alias` | To create an alias |
1 | `1-hello_you` | To prints `hello user`, where user is the current Linux user |
2 | `2-path` |To add `/action` to the `PATH`. `/action` should be the last directory the shell looks into when looking for a program |
3 | `3-paths` |to count the number of the directories in the `PATH` |
4 | `4-global_variables` |to lists environment variables |
5 | `5-local_variables` |to lists all local variables and environment variables, and functions |
6 | `6-create_local_variable` | to create a new local variable
7 | `7-create_global_variable` | to create a new global variable|
8 | `8-true_knowledge` | to print the result of the addition of 128 with the value stored in the environment variable `TRUEKNOWLEDGE`, followed by a new line |
9 | `9-divide_and_rule` | to print the result of `POWER` divided by `DIVIDE`, followed by a new line |
10 | `10-love_exponent_breath` | to display the result of `BREATH` to the power `LOVE` |
11 | `11-binary_to_decimal` | to convert a number from base 2 to base 10 |
12 | `12-combinations` | to print all possible combinations of two letters, except `oo` |
| `13-print_float` | to print a number with two decimal places. The number is stored in the environment variable `NUM` |
14 | `14-decimal_to_hexadecimal` | to convert a number from base 10 to base 16 |
15 | `100-rot13` | to encodes and decodes text using the rot13 encryption |
16 | `101-odd` | to print every other line from the input, starting with the first line |
17 | `102-water_and_str` | to add the two numbers stored in the environment variables `WATER` and `STIR` and prints the result |
